# XT.Net Conventions

This codebase uses XT.Net for XT cryptocurrency exchange access. Do not write raw `HttpClient` calls to XT endpoints.

## Client Setup Pattern

```csharp
using XT.Net;
using XT.Net.Clients;

var restClient = new XTRestClient(options =>
{
    options.ApiCredentials = new XTCredentials("API_KEY", "API_SECRET");
});
```

For public market data only, no credentials are needed: `new XTRestClient()`.

## Result Pattern

All methods return `WebCallResult<T>` or `WebCallResult` for REST and `CallResult<T>` for WebSocket. Always check `.Success` before reading `.Data`.

```csharp
var ticker = await restClient.SpotApi.ExchangeData.GetTickersAsync("eth_usdt");
if (!ticker.Success) { Console.WriteLine(ticker.Error); return; }
var first = ticker.Data.First();
```

## API Surface

- `restClient.SpotApi.{ExchangeData|Account|Trading}`
- `restClient.UsdtFuturesApi.{ExchangeData|Account|Trading}`
- `restClient.CoinFuturesApi.{ExchangeData|Account|Trading}`
- `socketClient.SpotApi`
- `socketClient.FuturesApi`

Do not generate `socketClient.UsdtFuturesApi` or `socketClient.CoinFuturesApi`; futures sockets are under `FuturesApi`.

## WebSocket Pattern

```csharp
var socketClient = new XTSocketClient();
var sub = await socketClient.SpotApi.SubscribeToTickerUpdatesAsync(
    "eth_usdt",
    update => Console.WriteLine(update.Data.LastPrice));
if (!sub.Success) { Console.WriteLine(sub.Error); return; }

await socketClient.UnsubscribeAsync(sub.Data);
```

Private spot streams need `restClient.SpotApi.Account.GetWebsocketTokenAsync()`. Private futures streams need `restClient.UsdtFuturesApi.Account.GetListenKeyAsync()`.

## Multi-Exchange Code

For exchange-agnostic code, use `CryptoExchange.Net.SharedApis`:

```csharp
using CryptoExchange.Net.SharedApis;

var shared = new XTRestClient().SpotApi.SharedClient;
var ticker = await shared.GetSpotTickerAsync(
    new GetTickerRequest(new SharedSymbol(TradingMode.Spot, "BTC", "USDT")));
```

## Hard Rules

- Never write raw `HttpClient` XT endpoint calls.
- Never use `.Result` or `.Wait()`; use `await`.
- Never instantiate clients per request; reuse or use DI.
- Never skip checking `WebCallResult.Success`.
- Always use `XTCredentials("key", "secret")`, not generic `ApiCredentials`.
- Always store WebSocket subscriptions and unsubscribe on shutdown.
- Always inspect `XT.Net/Interfaces/Clients/**` before generating methods not in the map.

